            <p><add hand="#barker">Commerce. Financial difficulty.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><date when="1817-09-06">Sept 6th 1817</date></p>
<p>Dear <persName>Son</persName>,</p>

<p><persName>Mr Donnal</persName> has recd from me 380 Dollares being the full amount
of the sale of your Whiskey, which on being gauged at <placeName>St Louis</placeName> did
not hold fully 40 Gall. I think something must be wrong in the
manner of gaugi[n]g the Whiskey at the <placeName>Still house</placeName>&#8212;</p>

<p>I Pray you to make a visit to <placeName>Herculanm </placeName>as soon as you can I have
had your Note renew.d&#8212;at the <placeName>Bank</placeName>&#8212;to Boring for 500 Dollars<pb n="321"/>
I start this moment to the <placeName>Mines </placeName>for your <persName>Mother </persName>shall return on
Monday next I wish you to give some kind of an answer about
the Beef and in my opinion you had better collect all you can and
send them forward to <placeName>St Louis</placeName> you Know the <date when="1817-10-15">15 of Octobr</date> is near
At Hand when <persName>Cox </persName>will be calling on us</p>

<p><persName>Moses Austin </persName>   [Rubric]</p>

<p>love to <persName>Emely </persName>and the <hi rend="italic"><persName>son</persName></hi></p>

<p>[Addressed:]<persName> Mr James Bryan</persName> <placeName>Hazel Run</placeName></p>

        </div1>
